definitions.definition: The act of conducting or carrying out ( business , negotiations , plans ).
examples: The transaction was made on Friday with the supplier.

definitions.definition: A deal or business agreement . (Can we add an example for this sense?)
An exchange or trade , as of ideas, money, goods, etc.
examples: I made the transaction with the vendor as soon as she showed me the pearls.

definitions.definition: The transfer of funds into, out of, or from an account .
An atomic operation ; a message, data modification, or other procedure that is guaranteed to perform completely or not at all (e.g. a database transaction ).
A record of the proceedings of a learned society .
